com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2

Interface ObjectWithPropagatorFunctions

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ObjectWithPropagatorFunctionsImpl

    public interface ObjectWithPropagatorFunctions
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    The interface that will be supported by all object using PropagatorFunction for maintaining the state of their derived elements.

    A PropagatorFunction maintains a collection of PropagatorFunction, responsible for maintaining specific derived elements. They can be added by calling following methods

    • method addPropagatorFunction(PropagatorFunction)
    • method #addPropagatorFunction(PropagatorFunction, boolean)
    • method #addPropagatorFunction(PropagatorFunction, EObject)
    The extra parameter can be used to indicate if the newly added PropagatorFunction must be touched at addition time.

    A given PropagatorFunction attached to this ObjectWithPropagatorFunctions may be retrieved by the methods

    • method getPropagatorFunction(EClass)
    • method getPropagatorFunction(Class)
    using the type of the to be retrieved PropagatorFunction as key. Presently, only the type of the PropagatorFunction can be used as key.

    The following features are supported:

    • Propagator Functions
    See Also:
    PropagatorPackage.getObjectWithPropagatorFunctions()

      • getPropagatorFunctions

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<PropagatorFunction> getPropagatorFunctions()
        Returns the value of the 'Propagator Functions' containment reference list. The list contents are of type PropagatorFunction. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Object With Propagator Functions'.

        If the meaning of the 'Propagator Functions' reference list isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...
